SP.P:
Sir, with your pardon, I cannot think it un∣filial or imprudent;
(with a most patriotic warmth)
I own, I do wish, most ardently wish, for a total ex∣tinction of all parties; particularly, that those of Eng∣lish, Irish, and Scotch, might never more be brought into contest or competition, unless like loving brothers, in general emulation for one common cause.
